race.comment: TEMPRANILLO (13) resumes for the Waller/Lane combination having shown ability last time in, getting out over a trip when narrowly beaten in a BM64 over 1900m at Canterbury before a break. No doubt 1200m is short of her best but she's back in a maiden and a fairly winnable one at that. AKA DAKA (2) resumes off a solid trial win at Tatura having been close to breaking through last time in. He is off nearly a year here so watch the market late for a guide. SEEING RED (16) was in the market on debut at Geelong but struggled and has been given a let up since. Trusting the market there and expecting improvement. ADIURO (1) is a 23 start maiden so tread carefully but his past two have been very good and he should run well. UNRIDDLE (6) improved nicely second up at Moe and should be ready to fire now.
